  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its recent publication in 2021 by Leuven University Press, \"The Global Horizon\" has observed relatively low engagement metrics, with no citations reported. However, the inferred scholarly uptake indicates a moderate engagement from the academic community, suggesting a potential for future impact in discussions of sustainability and policy relevance.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2021, \"The Global Horizon\" by Leuven University Press contributes to the discourse surrounding sustainability and global policy issues. Though it currently has no recorded citations, the presence of inferred roles highlights the book's relevance, particularly in sustainability and policy contexts, as evidenced by an associated metric indicating alignment with one of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's commercial availability on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads further underscores its potential accessibility to a broader audience, suggesting that the work could reach not only academics but also practitioners and the interested public. This commercial linkage adds a layer of potential impact, although formal engagements remain minimal to date.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As no high-fidelity social or community discourse metrics are present, it appears that discussions surrounding \"The Global Horizon\" are yet to flourish on platforms such as Reddit or Wikipedia. This absence indicates a need for more proactive engagement from the authors or publishing entity to stimulate broader conversations in relevant communities.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while the immediate impact metrics show low engagement, the inferred roles indicate that the book holds promise for engagement in sustainability discussions moving forward. Continued monitoring of citation trends and community discourse will be essential to fully gauge its influence in both academic and public spheres.</p>",
